The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for geospatial land classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of different augmentation techniques and class weights, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The datasets used in the experiments are related to remote sensing and geospatial analysis, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
